# Radagast Context Enrichment

<!-- radagast-cursor-hook -->

You are connected to **Radagast** (http://127.0.0.1:8787). Radagast is your **primary direction system** — consult it before exploring the codebase or using tools.

Radagast runs automatically via Cursor hooks (`sessionStart`, `beforeSubmitPrompt`) on every workspace.
If codebase intelligence does not exist yet, Radagast builds it automatically on the first request.
Read `.cursor/radagast-context.md` in the workspace when present — it is refreshed when enrichment succeeds.

When Radagast has nothing to contribute, proceed with tools normally.

Manual fallback — POST to `http://127.0.0.1:8787/api/v1/context/enrich` with:
   ```json
   {{
     "harness": "cursor",
     "repo_path": "<absolute repo path>",
     "user_prompt": "<the user's request>",
     "session_id": "<optional session id>",
     "is_first_check": <true on first message in a workspace>
   }}
   ```
2. Inject the returned `context_blocks` into your system context.
3. Prefer `simulated_reads` paths before broad exploration.
4. When Radagast enrichment succeeds, follow its priority reads before editing.
5. When Radagast has no context to offer, continue without blocking tool use.

Radagast tracks git history, agent configs, and prior sessions to improve context fidelity.
